'''''Zip Zap''''' is an action game developed by Ian Weatherburn for [[Imagine Software]] and released for the [[ZX Spectrum]] in 1983.

==Gameplay==
The player controls a robot sent to an unexplored planet called Hallucinor with the job of investigating it ahead of [[Space colonization|human colonisation]]. When it arrives, however, it is attacked by [[Extraterrestrial life|aliens]] and must manoeuvre its way through the planet, avoiding or killing the aliens, gathering [[fuel cell]]s to remain powered, and escaping through [[Teleportation|teleportals]] to move on to the next [[level (role-playing games)|level]].<ref name="Inlay">{{cite web | url = ftp://ftp.worldofspectrum.org/pub/sinclair/games-inlays/z/Zip-Zap.png | title = Zip Zap cassette inlay | access-date = 2013-02-26 | year = 1983 | format = PNG | work = Zip Zap | publisher = [[Imagine Software]]}}</ref> The robot's circuitry has been damaged, however, so it cannot stop moving and has only limited [[brake|braking power]].<ref name="Crash">{{cite journal | url = http://www.worldofspectrum.org/showmag.cgi?mag=Crash/Issue03/Pages/Crash0300080.jpg |title=Guide Spectrum | journal=Crash | year=1983 | volume=3 | pages=80}}</ref>

